comments: Gordon (DEN) does not step out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Gordon (DEN) places his left hand to the side of Curry (GSW) during the drive and the marginal contact has no affect on the ballhandler's SQBR.
Denver is unable to attempt a shot that makes contact with the rim prior to the expiration of the twenty-four second shot clock. Possession is correctly awarded to Golden State.
Jokic (DEN) legally contests the driving shot attempt by Curry (GSW).
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in the path of Payton II (DEN) and marginal contact occurs as the former firms up while setting the pick.
Payton II (GSW) makes contact with the forearm and wrist of Jokic (DEN) after the release of the floater attempt in the paint. The contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (GSW) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Jokic (DEN) brushes the back of Payton II (GSW) as he releases away from the defender after setting the pick.
Payton II (GSW) momentarily brings his right arm around the back of Jokic (DEN) and then slides it off during the post matchup.
Wiggins (GSW) extends his right arm into the midsection of Jokic (DEN) during the post shot attempt and the brief touch is marginal.
Morris (DEN) legally contests the driving shot attempt by Curry (GSW).
Green (DEN) establishes himself in a wide screening stance in the path of Payton II (DEN) and marginal leg to leg contact occurs when the latter fights over the top of the screen.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Curry (GSW) and some contact occurs as Curry trails his assignment around the pick.
Morris (DEN) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Green (DEN) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Payton II (GSW) commits a take foul on Morris (DEN).
Morris (DEN) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests the driving shot attempt by Morris (DEN), who loses his balance when he returns to the floor.
